  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TaC2">
<l>ulakupaṭait tuṇṭa vēntai yaṟaikaḻal</l>
<l>cuṭarppūn tāmarai cūṭutaṟ kavāvā</l>
<l>ruyiruruki yukka nēriya kāta</l>
<l>laṉpi liṉpīṉ tēṟa lamuta</l>
<l>veḷḷat tāṉāñ ciṟappuviṭ ṭoruporuṭ</l>
<l>kacaivō racaika tiruvoṭu maruviya</l>
<l>viyaṟkai māyāp peruviṟa lulaka</l>
<l>mūṉṟi ṉoṭunalvīṭu peṟiṉuṅ</l>
<l>koḷva teṇṇumō teḷḷiyōr kuṟippē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The [feet with] tinkling anklets of our father who created [and] ate the world,</l>
<l>those who long to wear [these] glowing flower lotuses,</l>
<l>leaving off [their] particularities, for the one wealth that is him on the flood</l>
<l>of clear ambrosia that brings forth pleasure in the love</l>
<l>that is the desire to meet [him], by which life is melted [and] shed,</l>
<l>let them, who move, move. Even if good liberation were to be obtained</l>
<l>along with [all] three of the vast victorious worlds that do not vanish,</l>
<l>of a nature to be joined with Śrī,</l>
<l>would the intention of those who are clear consider taking [it]?</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
